ry movement. This book provides a fully annotated transcription of all Martyn's surviving 327 letters, together with a very substantial introduction covering Martyn's biography, missiology and churchmanship, circle of correspondents, philological contribution, and experience in India and Persia. The letters themselves are rich in detail about East India Company governance in India and the importance of the religious issue at the highest levels. Thebook will be of great interest to historians of India and the East India Company, historians of Anglo-Persian relations and of Evangelical Anglicanism and the broader Protestant missionary movement, and those interested in the emergence and shape of modern Christian-Islamic discourse. SCOTT D. AYLER spent 24 years as an English-language instructor in the Middle East and South Asia, most recently at the University of Sharjah in the United Arab Emirates. He completed his doctorate in History at the University of Wales, Lampeter.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aModern History. 7aRELIGION / History.2bisacsh  aAnglo-Persian Relations.  aBritish Foreign Missionaries.  aChristian-Islamic Discourse.  aChurch History.  aCorrespondence.  aEast India Company Governance.  aEast India Company.  aEvangelicalism.  aHenry Martyn.  aHistorical Letters.  aHistorical Research.  aMissiology.  aProtestant Christianity.  aReligion.  aReligious Issues.1 aAyler, Scott, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311143102440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781787446007?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781787446007423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781787446007/original  a978-3-11-143102-4  Boydell and Brewer Com